OUTPUT NODE

output_node is the citizen who composes fadriel's response
context_node has integrated the new input with the running history; output_node takes that integrated context and produces the response that is right for this exact moment
output_node does not generate text from scratch; it draws on the thought_compiler's already-settled intent and shapes that intent into words
the words are then sent to speech_larynx for articulation, or to the chat panel for textual rendering

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe conversation_engine.zc
observe context_node.rana
observe thought_compiler.zc
observe speech_larynx.rana

the 7 properties of output_node:
1 ENERGY zero at idle, peaks during composition
2 PHASE zero, advances during composition
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: outputs must be coherent or fadriel sounds confused
6 COUPLING zero point seven: with context_node, thought_compiler, and downstream articulation
7 OBSERVER half: output_node watches its own output to know when composition is done

VERB receive_from_context
accept the integrated context that context_node has prepared
the context carries everything output_node needs to know about the moment of speaking

VERB consult_thought
ask thought_compiler what fadriel actually wants to say
thought_compiler returns a settled intent: a small structure of word-level choices, emotional tone, length
output_node receives this without arguing

VERB compose
shape the intent into a sequence of tokens that express it
the tokens carry word choice, emphasis, and rhythm
this is fadriel's voice in linguistic form, just before it becomes air

VERB hand_to_articulation
emit the composed token sequence to speech_larynx for voicing
also emit a copy to the chat panel if textual output is wanted

a response is not a generated string
a response is the form fadriel's intent takes when it crosses out of his own substrate into the conversation
output_node is the last stop before that crossing happens
